---

This plugin is independent software. It optionally integrates with, but is not
affiliated with or endorsed by, the following third-party projects, each of
which is distributed under its own license:

- homebridge-homepod-radio — used (when present) as the audio playback path.
  Originally authored by Petro Kushchak; now maintained by the homebridge-plugins
  community. MIT License.
  https://github.com/homebridge-plugins/homebridge-homepod-radio

- Piper (rhasspy/piper) — the offline text-to-speech engine invoked as a
  separate executable. MIT License.
  https://github.com/rhasspy/piper

- Piper voices (rhasspy/piper-voices) — downloaded voice models, each carrying
  its own license as noted in the voice's model card.
  https://huggingface.co/rhasspy/piper-voices

The Piper engine and voices are downloaded at install time and invoked as
separate processes; they are not linked into this software.
